en_993711_0	To coincide with the ongoing ‘Wana Ropa’ national tree planting drive, Mechanized Infantry Regiment at Dambulla launched a tree sapling planting programme inside the Regimental Centre premises on Sunday (4).
en_993711_1	The event was organized under the directions of the Colonel of the Regiment Brigadier Sumith Atapattu and close supervision of the Overlooking Centre Commandant Lieutenant Colonel K.K.S Perakum.
en_993711_2	The project was sponsored by Defence Services Disabled Officers Association.
en_993711_3	During the brief ceremony, headed by the Colonel of the Regiment, Senior Officers and Other Ranks who are serving in the Regimental Centre planted about 1800 saplings as the 1st phase of the programme.
